that it's more likely to warp.

08:44.023 --> 08:46.234
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:46.234 --> 08:49.029
<i>‐ I cut off a piece</i>
<i>of mild steel off the frame</i>

08:49.029 --> 08:51.364
<i>and MIG welded it to the tang.</i>

08:51.364 --> 08:54.075
As I see it getting
a glassy look,

08:54.075 --> 08:57.037
<i>I'm realizing that now</i>
<i>I'm in a good space</i>

08:57.037 --> 08:59.706
where I can bring it out
and forge weld it all together.

08:59.706 --> 09:01.374
<i>I don't believe the mild steel</i>

09:01.374 --> 09:03.084
is gonna affect
the tang whatsoever.

09:03.084 --> 09:05.795
‐ It looks like Steve decided

09:05.795 --> 09:07.756
to put the mild steel
on the tang.

09:07.756 --> 09:10.425
Would you weld it
on the hard steel,

09:10.425 --> 09:12.552
