the length for the blade?

09:26.900 --> 09:31.571
It looks close to 11 inches.
I don't know.

09:31.571 --> 09:32.906
‐ You getting there?

09:32.906 --> 09:34.407
‐ Yeah, I'm ready
to forge‐weld.

09:34.407 --> 09:35.992
‐ There you go.
‐ Doing all right?

09:35.992 --> 09:37.410
You already get a weld on it?
‐ Oh, yeah.

09:37.410 --> 09:39.245
I'm gonna use
a piece of mild steel

09:39.245 --> 09:41.915
from the frame in the handle.

09:41.915 --> 09:44.667
Being that the test
is a plate chop,

09:44.667 --> 09:46.878
<i>I'm putting the mild steel</i>
<i>in the handle.</i>

09:46.878 --> 09:49.589
<i>That way, when it takes</i>
<i>that big jolt,</i>

09:49.589 --> 09:52.050
